{"parse":{"title":"orange","pageid":1557,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|orange|orangé|Orange|Orangë}}\n==English==\n[[File:Color icon orange.svg|thumb|upright|Various shades of orange.]]\n[[File:Ambersweet oranges.jpg|thumb|upright|Some oranges (the fruits).]]\n[[File:Orange_tree_in_Menton.jpg|thumb|upright|An orange tree.]]\n{{Wiktionary:Picture dictionary/en:color}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|aurange|oreche|orenche|orendge|oreng|oringe|orrendge|orrenge|orring|orringe|orryge|orrynge|urring||all|_|obsolete}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|en|id=fruit|:inh|enm:orenge<id:fruit>|tree=1}}\n{{inh+|en|enm|orenge}}, {{m|enm|orange}}, from {{der|en|fro|pome orenge|t=fruit orange}}, influenced by the place name {{m|en|Orange}} (which is from Gaulish and unrelated to the word for the fruit and colour) and by {{der|en|pro|auranja}} and calqued from {{der|en|roa-oit|melarancio}}, {{m|it|melarancia}}, compound of {{m|it|mela|t=apple}} and {{m|it|[[un]]'[[arancia]]|t=an orange}}, from {{der|en|ar|نَارَنْج}}, from Early {{der|en|fa-cls|نَارَنْگْ}}, from {{der|en|sa|नारङ्ग|t=orange tree}},<ref name=\"OnlineED\">{{R:Online Etymology Dictionary|entry=orange}}</ref> ultimately from {{der|en|dra}}. Compare {{cog|ta|நாரங்காய்}}, compound of {{m|ta|நாரம்|t=water}} and {{m|ta|காய்|t=fruit}}; also {{cog|te|నారంగము, నారింజ}}, {{cog|ml|നാരങ്ങ}}, {{cog|kn|ನಾರಂಗಿ}}).\n\nOriginally borrowed as the surname (derived from the place name) in the 13th century, before the sense of the fruit was imported in the late 14th century and the colour in 1510.<ref name=\"OnlineED\"/> In the colour sense, largely displaced {{m|ang|ġeolurēad}}, whence {{m|en|yellow-red}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|ŏrʹĭnj|ŏrʹənj|a=RP}}; {{IPA|en|/ˈɒɹɪnd͡ʒ/|/ˈɒɹənd͡ʒ/|/ˈɒɹɪnʒ/|/ˈɒɹənʒ/}}\n** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Back ache-ORANGE.wav|a=UK|IPA=/ˈɒɹɪnd͡ʒ/}}\n* {{enPR|ôrʹĭnj|a=GA,CA}}; {{IPA|en|/ˈɔɹənd͡ʒ/|/ˈɔɹn̩d͡ʒ/|/ɔɹnd͡ʒ/}}\n** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Aquild-orange.wav|a=Pacific Northwest|IPA=/ˈɔɹənd͡ʒ/}}\n* {{enPR|ärʹĭnj|ŏrʹĭnj|a=US,East Coast}}; {{IPA|en|/ˈɑɹənd͡ʒ/|/ˈɑɹəŋʒ/}}\n** {{audio|en|En-NYC-orange.wav|a=NYC}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈɔɹɪnd͡ʒ/|a=AU}}\n* {{enPR|ˈoɹeɪnd͡ʒ|a=Philippines}}\n* {{homophones|en|Orange}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɒɹɪndʒ|ɒɹəndʒ|s=2}} {{q|see [[#Usage notes|notes]]}}\n* {{hyph|en|or|ange}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{lb|en|countable}} An [[evergreen]] [[tree]] of the genus ''[[Citrus]]'' such as {{taxfmt|Citrus sinensis|species}} which yields oranges (the fruit).\n# {{senseid|en|Q13191}}{{lb|en|countable}} Any round [[citrus]] [[fruit]] with a yellow-red colour when ripe and a sour-sweet taste; the fruit of the orange tree.\n## {{lb|en|countable}} Specifically, a [[sweet orange]] or {{taxfmt|Citrus sinensis|species}}.\n# {{senseid|en|Q39338}}{{lb|en|uncountable}} The [[colour]] of a ripe fruit of an orange tree, midway between red and yellow.\n#: {{color panel|FF8000}}\n#: {{syn|en|yellow-red}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable}} {{n-g|Various drinks:}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|date=2015-03-31|author=Debbie McGowan|title=Two By Two|publisher=Beaten Track Publishing|isbn=9781910635414|page=81\n|text=“What you drinking?” “'''Orange''' and soda will go down nicely, thanks.” “Pint?” “Sure.” Andy headed for the bar, stopping along the way to kiss Shaunna and check she and Kris were OK for a drink. “Everything all right?” Sean asked.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|date=2015-05-07|author=Tosh Lavery|title=Tosh: An Amazing True Story Of Life, Death, Danger And Drama In The Garda Sub-Aqua Unit|publisher=Penguin UK|isbn=9781844883592\n|text=I ran out into the street and around the block, searching everywhere, and finally burst into O'Dowd's pub around the corner to see Thomas sitting at the bar drinking '''orange''' and eating a bag of crisps with two old men.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|date=2018-05-25|author=Michael Nilsen|title=Beyond the Cave|publisher=Troubador Publishing Ltd|isbn=9781789014211|page=82\n|text=It transpired this lad was drinking '''orange''' and faculties were keen. There were one or two verbal exchanges, then I followed him into the car park. He said to the doorman, 'I won't be long.' He easily knocked me to the ground.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|date=2021-06-10|author=Anna McPartlin|title=Waiting for the Miracle: Warm your heart this winter with this uplifting novel from the bestselling author of THE LAST DAYS OF RABBIT HAYES|publisher=Bonnier Zaffre Ltd.|isbn=9781838773915\n|text=When the fast songs played, like the Beatles' 'Help' or The Rolling Stones' 'Satisfaction', Justin and I sat on two wooden chairs, drinking '''orange''' and holding hands. When the nuns weren't watching, I rested my head on his shoulder.}}\n## An orange-coloured and orange-flavoured [[cordial]].\n## An orange-coloured and orange-flavoured [[soft drink]].\n## {{lb|en|uncommon}} Orange juice.\n# {{lb|en|heraldry}} A rarely-used nontraditional tincture found in Catalan, South African, and French municipal heraldry.\n# {{lb|en|heraldry}} An orange-coloured [[roundel]].\n#* {{see citations|en}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* It is commonly stated that ''orange'' has no rhymes. While there are no commonly used English dictionary words that rhyme exactly with ''orange'' ({{m|en|door hinge}} comes close in US pronunciation), see [[Rhymes:English/ɒɹɪndʒ]] for some possibilities. See also [[w:Orange_(word)#Rhyme|the Wikipedia article about rhymes for the word ''orange'']].\n* In most dialects, ''orange'' is pronounced with two syllables.  But in certain dialects of North American English, the vowel of the second syllable is deleted and the word is pronounced as one syllable.<ref>https://www.merriam-webster.com/words-at-play/what-rhymes-with-orange</ref> In such dialects, the two forms are generally {{l|en|allophony|allophonic}}.\n\n====Hypernyms====\n* [[Thesaurus:fruit|fruit]]\n** {{l|en|citrus}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col2|en\n| acridine orange|[[African cherry orange]] ({{taxlink|Citropsis articulata|species}})|[[Alpine grassland orange]] ({{taxlink|Aponotoreas insignis|species}})\n| {{vern|bergamot orange}} ({{taxlink|Citrus bergamia|species}})|bitter orange|blaze orange|[[blood orange]] ({{taxfmt|Citrus sinensis|species}})|blorange|bog orange|{{vern|box orange}} ({{taxlink|Severinia buxifolia|species}})|burnt orange\n| cadmium orange|{{vern|calamondin orange}} (×{{taxlink|Citrofortunella microcarpa|nothospecies}})|cherry orange|[[China orange]] (×{{taxlink|Citrofortunella microcarpa|nothospecies}})|chrome orange|citrange|clockwork orange|coolie orange|Cox's Orange Pippin\n| direct orange\n| East Orange|emergency orange\n| {{vern|green orange}} ({{taxlink|Citrus reticulata × sinensis|nothospecies}})\n| {{vern|hardy orange}} ({{taxlink|Citrus trifoliata|species}}, syn. {{taxlink|Poncirus trifoliata|species}})|{{vern|horned orange}}\n| international orange\n| Jaffa orange\n| light orange|Lombard Street to a China orange\n| [[mandarin orange]] ({{taxfmt|Citrus reticulata|species}})|methyl orange|Mexican orange|[[mock orange]], [[mock-orange]] ({{taxfmt|Maclura pomifera|species}}, {{taxfmt|Philadelphus|genus}} spp., etc.)|[[monkey orange]] ({{taxfmt|Maclura pomifera|species}})\n| naphthol orange|[[Natal orange]] ({{taxlink|Strychnos spinosa|species}})|{{vern|native orange}} ({{taxlink|Pittosporum pauciflorum|species}}, syn. {{taxlink|Citriobatus parviflorus|species}})|navel orange\n| orangeade|orange-aise|orange-American,orange American\n| orange badge|orange ball buddleja|orange-ball-tree|orange-bellied parrot|{{vern|orange bird}} ({{taxlink|Tanagra zena|species}})|orange blister beetle|orange blossom|orange blossom water|Orange Bowl|orange box\n| {{vern|orange cestrum}} ({{taxlink|Cestrum aurantiacum|species}})|orange chicken|orange chromide|{{vern|orange cowry}} ({{taxlink|Cypraea aurantia|species}})|orange-crowned warbler\n| orange daisy|orange dog|orange drink\n| orange filefish|[[orange flowering jessamine]] ({{taxlink|Cestrum aurantiacum|species}})|orange flower water|orange-footed scrubfowl|Orange Free State\n| orange goods|{{vern|orange grass}} ({{taxlink|Hypericum sarothra|species}})|orange grove,Orange Grove|[[orange gum]] ({{taxlink|Angophora lanceolata|species}}\n| [[orange hawkweed]] ({{taxlink|Pilosella aurantiaca|species}}, syn. {{taxlink|Hieracium aurantiacum|species}})\n|Orangies|orangish\n| [[orange jessamine]] ({{taxlink|Cestrum aurantiacum|species}})|orange juice\n| orangeless|orange lily|Orange lodge\n| Orangeman<!--Not the same as \"Orange Man\".-->|Orange Man<!--Not the same as \"Orangeman\".-->|[[orange milkweed]] ({{taxfmt|Asclepias tuberosa|species}})|orange mint\n| orange notice\n| orange ochre|Orange Order\n| orange peel,orange-peel|orange-peel bucket|orange-peel fungus|orange peel theory|orange-peely|orange pekoe|orange pill|orange pipefish|orange puppy\n| orangequat\n| Orange Revolution|orange ringlet|orangerita|Orange River|[[orangeroot]] ({{taxlink|Hydrastis canadensis|species}})|orange roughy|orangery\n| {{vern|orange scale}} ({{taxlink|Lepidosaphes beckii|species}})|[[orange sharpshooter]] ({{taxlink|Bothrogonia addita|species}})|orange-spotted bulbul|orange-spotted drone fly|orange squash|[[orange staff sergeant]] ({{taxlink|Athyma cama|species}})|orange stick|orange sunshine|orange swift\n| orange-thighed frog|{{vern|orange thorn}} ({{taxlink|Pittosporum pauciflorum|species}}, syn. {{taxlink|Citriobatus parviflorus|species}})|orange-throated whiptail|orangetini|orange-tip,orange tip|orange tree\n| orange-wife|orange wine|orange-winged amazon|orange-winged parrot|orangewood\n| Orangey,orangey\n| [[Osage orange]], [[osage orange]], [[osage-orange]] ({{taxfmt|Maclura pomifera|species}})|{{vern|Otaheite orange}} ({{taxlink|Citrus limonia|species}})\n| Persian orange|Princeton orange\n| queer as a clockwork orange|{{vern|Quito orange}} ({{taxfmt|Solanum quitoense|species}})\n| safety orange|{{vern|satsuma orange}} ({{taxfmt|Citrus unshiu|species}})|[[sea orange]] ({{taxlink|Psolus fabricii|species}})|[[Seville orange]] ({{taxfmt|Citrus aurantium|species}})|{{vern|soap orange}} ({{taxlink|Citrus aurantium saponacea|subspecies}})|sooty orange tip|{{vern|sour orange}} ({{taxfmt|Citrus ×aurantium|nothospecies}})|{{vern|spring orange}} ({{taxlink|Styrax americana|species}})|sunset orange|Super Orange|[[sweet orange]] ({{taxfmt|Citrus sinensis|species}})\n| tachibana orange|temple orange|there's more than one way to peel an orange|[[trifoliate orange]] ({{taxlink|Citrus trifoliata|species}}, syn. {{taxlink|Poncirus trifoliata|species}})\n| Valencia orange\n| wild orange\n| xylenol orange\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|bor=1|eo|oranĝo}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|haw|ʻalani}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|ja|オレンジ|tr=orenji}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|csb|orendż|qq=Canada, United States}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|ko|오렌지}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|myh|ʔo·linčas}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|ms|oren|oyen}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|mh|oran}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|ta|ஆரஞ்சு}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|unm|òlënch}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|tree}}\n{{multitrans|data=\n* Afrikaans: {{tt|af|lemoenboom}}\n* Antillean Creole: {{t|gcf|oranjé|m}}, {{t|gcf|owanjé|m}} {{t|gcf|pyé zoranj}}\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|شَجَرَةْ اَلْبُرْتُقَال|f}}, {{tt+|ar|بُرْتُقَالَة|f}}, {{tt|ar|نَارَنْج}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{tt|aii|ܐܝܼܠܵܢܵܐ ܕܦܘܼܪܬܩܵܠܵܐ|tr=īlānā d-purtqālā}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|նարինջ}}\n* Asturian: {{tt+|ast|naranxal|m|f}}, {{tt+|ast|ñaranxal|m|f}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|portağal}}\n* Basque: {{tt+|eu|laranjondo}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|апэльсі́навае дрэ́ва|n}}\n* Breton: {{tt+|br|gwezenn-orañjez|f}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|портокал|m}}\n* Burmese: {{tt+|my|လိမ္မော်}}, {{tt+|my|ကမ္ဗလာ}}\n* Catalan: {{tt|ca|taronger|m}}\n* Chechen: {{tt|ce|апельсин}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{tt|yue|橙樹|tr=caang4-2 syu6}}\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|橙樹|tr=chéngshù}}\n* Comorian:\n*: Ngazidja Comorian: {{tt|zdj|mrunɗa|c3|c4}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|pomerančovník|m}}\n* Danish: {{tt|da|appelsintræ}}\n* Dhivehi: {{t|dv|އޮރެންޖުގަސް|s}}, {{t|dv|އޮރެންޖުގަސްތައް|p}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|sinaasappelboom|m}}, {{tt+|nl|appelsienenboom|m}}\n* Erzya: {{tt|myv|сырнемарь чувто}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt+|eo|oranĝarbo}}, {{tt|eo|oranĝujo}}\n* Estonian: {{tt+|et|apelsinipuu}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|appelsiinipuu}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|oranger|m}}\n* Gagauz: {{tt|gag|portokal}}\n* Galician: {{tt+|gl|laranxeira|f}}\n* Gallurese: {{tt|sdn|aranzu}}\n* Georgian: {{tt+|ka|ფორთოხალი}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Apfelsinenbaum|m}}, {{tt+|de|Orangenbaum|m}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|πορτοκαλιά|f}}\n*: Pontic Greek: {{t|pnt|πορτοκαλέα}}\n* Haitian Creole: {{tt|ht|zoranj}}\n* Hawaiian: {{tt|haw|ʻalani}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|תפוז|m|tr=tapúz}}\n* Hindi: {{tt+|hi|नारंगी|f}}, {{tt+|hi|संतरा|m}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|narancsfa}}\n* Hunsrik: {{tt|hrx|Ranschebaam|m}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt|is|appelsínutré|n}}\n* Ido: {{tt+|io|oranjiero}}\n* Indonesian: {{tt+|id|jeruk manis}}\n* Irish: {{tt|ga|crann oráistí|m}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|arancio|m}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|蜜柑|tr=みかん, mikan}}, {{tt+|ja|橙|tr=だいだい, daidai}}, {{tt+|ja|オレンジ|tr=orenji}}, {{tt+|ja|橘|tr=たちばな, tachibana}}\n* Kashubian: {{tt+|csb|apfelzyna}}\n* Korean: {{tt|ko|오렌지-나무}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{tt|ckb|دار پرتەقاڵ}}\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{tt+|kmr|pirteqal}}\n* Laz: {{t|lzz|ფოტუკალი}}\n* Lithuanian: {{tt|lt|apelsinmedis|m}}\n* Low German: {{tt|nds|Appelsien|f}}, {{tt|nds|Orange|f}}\n* Luxembourgish: {{tt|lb|Orangëbam|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt+|mk|портокал|m}}\n* Malay: {{tt|ms|pokok limau}}\n* Malayalam: {{tt|ml|മധുര നാരകം}}, {{tt|ml|ഓറഞ്ച് മരം}}\n* Maltese: {{tt|mt|larinġa|f}}\n* Nahuatl: {{tt|nah|lalaxcuahuitl}}\n* Navajo: {{tt|nv|chʼil łitsxooí}}\n* Norman: {{tt|nrf|orangyi|m}} {{qualifier|Jersey}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt|nb|appelsintre|n}}\n* Occitan:\n*: Old Occitan: {{tt|pro|auranja}}\n* Persian:\n*: Dari: {{tt|prs|مَالْتَه}}\n*: Iranian Persian: {{tt|fa-ira|نارَنْج}}, {{tt|fa-ira|پُرْتِقال}}, {{tt|fa-ira|پُرْتُقال}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|pomarańcza|f}}, {{tt|pl|drzewo pomarańczowe|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|laranjeira|f}}\n* Quechua: {{tt|qu|aruma}}, {{tt|qu|laranqa}}, {{tt|qu|willapi}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|portocal|m}}\n* Russian: {{tt|ru|апельси́новое де́рево|n}}, {{tt+|ru|апельси́н|m}}\n* Sanskrit: {{tt+|sa|नारङ्ग|m}}\n* Sardinian: {{tt|sc|arbule de aranzu|m}}\n*: Campidanese: {{tt|sc|arangiu}}\n*: Logudorese: {{tt|sc|arancio}}\n* Sassarese: {{tt|sdc|aranzu}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|на̀ра̄нџа|f}}, {{tt|sh|помо̀ра̄нџа|f}}, {{tt|sh|на̀ра̄нча|f}}, {{tt|sh|помо̀ра̄нча|f}}\n*: Latin: {{tt|sh|nàrāndža|f}}, {{tt|sh|pomòrāndža|f}}, {{tt+|sh|nàrānča|f}}, {{tt|sh|pomòrānča|f}}\n* Sicilian: {{tt|scn|arancia|f}}, {{tt|scn|aranciara|f}}, {{tt|scn|àrburu di l'aranciu|m}}, {{tt|scn|macchia di l'aranciu|f}}\n* Sindhi: {{tt|sd|نارنگيءَ جو وَڻُ|m|tr=narangi’a ju vanu}}\n* Sinhalese: {{t+|si|දොඩම්}}\n* Slovak: {{tt+|sk|pomaranč|m}}\n* Slovene: {{tt+|sl|pomaranča|f}}\n* Somali: {{t+|so|liin}}\n* Sotho: {{tt|st|sefate sa lamunu}}\n* Southern Altai: {{t|alt|апельсин}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|naranjo|m}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|mchungwa}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|apelsinträd|n}}\n* Telugu: {{t|te|నారింజచెట్టు}}, {{t+|te|నారంగము}}\n* Thai: {{tt|th|ต้นส้ม|tr=dtôn-sôm}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|portakal}}\n* Turkmen: {{tt+|tk|apelsin}}, {{t|tk|pyrtykal}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|апельси́н|m}}, {{tt|uk|помара́нча|f}}\n* Vietnamese: ([[cây]]) {{tt+|vi|cam}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|oren}}\n* Yucatec Maya: {{tt|yua|china}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|fruit}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|lemoen}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|portokall|m}}\n* American Sign Language: {{tt|ase|C@NearChin Squeeze}}\n* Antillean Creole: {{t|gcf|oranj|f}}, {{t|gcf|owanj|f}}\n* Arabic: {{tt+|ar|بُرْتُقَال|m}} {{qualifier|collective}}, {{tt+|ar|بُرْتُقَالَة|f}} (''[[singulative]]'')\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{tt|arz|برتقان|tr=burtuʔān}} {{qualifier|collective}}, {{tt|arz|برتقانة|f|tr=burtuʔāna}} (''singulative'')\n*: Gulf Arabic: {{tt|afb|برتقال|m|tr=burtaqāl}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{tt|acw|بُرْتُقالة|f|tr=burtuqāla}}, {{qualifier|collective}} {{tt|acw|بُرْتُقال|m|tr=burtuqāla, burt