n: {{t+|br|orañjez}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|портока́лов}}, {{t+|bg|ора́нжев}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|ataronjat}}, {{t+|ca|carabassa}}, {{t+|ca|taronja}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t|yue|橙色|tr=caang4-2 sik1}}\n*: Hokkien: {{t+|nan-hbl|柑仔色|tr=kam-á-sek}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|橙色|tr=chéngsè}}, {{t+|cmn|橙黃色|tr=chénghuángsè}}, {{t+|cmn|橘黃色|tr=júhuángsè}}\n* Cornish: {{t|kw|rudhvelyn}}, {{t|kw|melynrudh}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|oranžový}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|orange}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|oranje}}, {{t|nl|brandgeel}}, {{t+|nl|geelrood}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|oranĝa}}, {{t+|eo|oranĝokolora}}, {{t+|eo|oranĝkolora}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|oranž}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|oranssi}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|orange}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|laranxa}}\n* German: {{t+|de|orange}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|πορτοκαλής|n}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|κιρρός}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|כתום|tr=katóm}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|नारंगी}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|narancssárga}}, {{t+|hu|narancsszínű}}\n* Hunsrik: {{t|hrx|ranschegelleb}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|appelsínugulur|m}}\n* Ido: {{t+|io|oranjea}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|jingga}}, {{t+|id|oranye}}\n* Irish: {{t+|ga|oráiste}}, {{t+|ga|flannbhuí}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|arancione}}, {{t+|it|arancio}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|オレンジ色|alt=オレンジ色の|tr=orenji-iro no}}, {{t+|ja|橙色|alt=橙色の|tr=だいだいいろの, daidai-iro-no}}\n* Khmer: {{t|km|ពណ៌លឿង|tr=poa lɨəng}}\n* Korean: {{t|ko|[[주황색(朱黃色)]]-의}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|aurantius}}\n* Latvian: {{t+|lv|oranžs}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t|lt|oranžinis}}\n* Louisiana Creole: {{t|lou|zoranj}}\n* Low German: {{t|nds|orange}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|портокалов}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|jingga}}\n* Manx: {{t|gv|oranje-vuigh}}\n* Māori: {{t+|mi|karaka}}\n* Marathi: {{t+|mr|नारंगी}}\n* Norman: {{t|nrf|orange}} {{qualifier|Jersey, Guernsey}}, {{t|nrf|oraunge}} {{qualifier|Cotentin}}\n* Norwegian: {{t+|no|oransje}}\n* Pashto: {{t+|ps|نارنجي|tr=nârënji}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|نارنجی|tr=nârenji}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|pomarańczowy}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|laranja}}, {{t|pt|laranjado}}, {{t+|pt|alaranjado}}, {{t+|pt|cor-de-laranja}}\n* Quechua: {{t|qu|killmu}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|portocaliu}}, {{t+|ro|oranj}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|ора́нжевый}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|orainds}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|на̀ра̄нџаст}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|nàrāndžast}}\n* Silesian: {{t|szl|apluzinowy}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|oranžový}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|oranžen}}\n* Southern Altai: {{t|alt|кызыл-сары}}, {{t|alt|кыскылтым-сары}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|anaranjado}}, {{t+|es|naranja}}, {{t|es|naranjado}} {{qualifier|Spain}}, {{t|es|naranjoso}}\n* Sranan Tongo: {{t|srn|alanya}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|machungwa}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|orange}}, {{t+|sv|brandgul}}, {{t+|sv|apelsinfärgad}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|ส้ม}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|turuncu}}, {{t+|tr|portakal rengi}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|жовтогаря́чий}},  {{t+|uk|ора́нжевий}}, {{t+|uk|помара́нчевий}}\n* Unami: {{t|unm|òlënchikte}} {{qualifier|inanimate}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|نارنگی|tr=nāraṅgī}}\n* Venetan: {{t|vec|narança}}, {{t|vec|narançon}}, {{t|vec|orans}}, {{t|vec|arancion}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t-check|vi|[[màu]] [[cam]]}} <!-- was \"[[màu]] [[cam]]\" - assumed sum-of-parts; if an idiom, use {{t}} instead of {{t-SOP}}. see [[User:Kephir/gadgets/xte#Translation_fixing]] -->\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|rojanik}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|oren}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|אָראַנזש}}\n* Yoruba: {{t|yo|bí ọsán}}, {{t|yo|bí òrombó}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To colour orange.\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Cinema: The movement-image|page=118|author=Gilles Deleuze|year=1986|passage=It is this composition which reaches a colourist perfection in Le Bonheur with the complementarity of violet, purple and '''oranged''' gold}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Rifles for Watie|page=256|author=Harold Keith|year=1987|passage=Jeff winked his eyes sleepily open and looked out into the cool flush of early morning. The east was '''oranged''' over with daybreak.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=The Very Ordered Existence of Merilee Marvelous|page=117|author=Suzanne Crowley|year=2009|passage=I looked at him through my binoculars, his little lips '''oranged''' with Cheeto dust.}}\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To become orange.\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Day in day out|page=296|author=Terézia Mora|year=2007|passage=Cranes in the distance against the background of the slowly '''oranging''' sky}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Jazz & twelve o'clock tales: new stories|page=14|author=Wanda Coleman|year=2008|passage=It will be followed by a disappearance of the cash I had hidden in a sealed envelope behind the '''oranging''' Modigliani print over the living room couch.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=The Passage|page=330|author=Justin Cronin|year=2010|passage=\"What about his eyes?\" / \"Nothing. No '''oranging''' at all, from what I could see.}}\n\n===See also===\n{{col|en\n|citrus\n|clementine\n|Cointreau\n|curaçao\n|mandarin\n|marmalade\n|murcott\n|naartjie\n|ortanique\n|pomander\n|satsuma\n|satsuma mandarin\n|satsuma tangerine\n|secondary colour\n|tangerine\n|triple sec\n|zest\n}}\n{{table:colors/en}}\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n* {{pedia}}\n* [https://starlingdb.org/cgi-bin/response.cgi?root=config&morpho=0&basename=\\data\\drav\\sdret&first=1981 South Dravidian Etymology] Sergei & George Starostin, 1998-2013.\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aegnor|Gerona|Gorean|Ragone|groane|onager}}\n\n{{C|en|Citrus subfamily plants|Colors of the rainbow|Fruits|Oranges}}\n\n==Danish==\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{bor|da|fr|orange}}, ultimately from {{der|da|dra}}. Compare {{cog|ta|நாரங்காய்}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|da|[oˈʁɑŋɕə]}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{da-noun|n|r}}\n\n# {{l|en|orange}} {{q|the taste of an orange}}\n# {{lb|da|rare}} {{l|en|orange}} {{gloss|fruit}}\n#: {{syn|da|appelsin}}\n\n===Declension===\n{{da-noun-infl|n|r}}\n\n===Derived terms===\n*{{l|da|orangeglaseret}}\n*{{l|da|orangesmag}}\n*{{l|da|orangesauce}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom the [[noun]] above.\n\n===Adjective===\n{{head|da|adjective|indeclinable}}\n\n# [[orange#Adjective|orange]] {{gloss|orange-coloured}}\n# {{lb|da|as a noun}} {{l|en|orange}} {{gloss|color}}\n\n===Declension===\n{{da-adj-infl}}\n\n===Derived terms===\n*{{l|da|gulorange}}\n*{{l|da|rødorange}}\n\n===See also===\n{{table:colors/da}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:DDO}}\n\n{{C|da|Fruits}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|fr|:inh|frm:orange<id:fruit>|id=fruit}}\n{{inh+|fr|frm|orange}}, from {{inh|fr|fro|orenge}}, short form of late {{m|fro|pomme d'orenge}} or ''pomme d'orange'', which was calqued after {{der|fr|roa-oit|melarancia}} ({{m|it|mela}} + {{m|it|arancia}}). The ''o'' came into the word under influence of the place name {{m|fr|Orange}}.\nSee {{m+|en|orange}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA}}\n* {{audio|fr|Fr-orange.ogg}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-DSwissK-orange.wav|a=<<Switzerland>> (<<Valais>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-GrandCelinien-orange.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Paris>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Lepticed7-orange.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Toulouse>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-LoquaxFR-orange.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Lyokoï-orange.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Mecanautes-orange.wav|a=France}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Poslovitch-orange.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-WikiLucas00-orange.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Jérémy-Günther-Heinz Jähnick-orange.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Somain>>)}}\n* {{rhymes|fr|ɑ̃ʒ|s=2}}\n* {{homophones|fr|orangent|oranges}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|f}}\n\n# {{l|en|orange}} {{gloss|fruit}}\n#: {{ux|fr|Il pressa l’'''orange''' afin d’en extraire du jus.|t=He squeezed the '''orange''' to extract juice from it.}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|ht|zoranj}}\n* {{desc|lou|zoranj}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|br|orañjez}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|be|ара́нжавы}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|bg|ора́нжев}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|da|orange}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|de|Orange}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|hrx|Ransch}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|lv|oranžs}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|nds|Orange}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|lb|Orange}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|no|oransje}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|ro|oranj}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|ru|ора́нжевый}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|sv|orange}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# {{l|en|orange}} {{gloss|colour}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|fr|oranger}}\n* {{w|Orangina}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{fr-adj|inv=1}}\n\n# [[orange#Adjective|orange]] {{gloss|orange-coloured}}\n#: {{ux|fr|Les premiers TGV atlantiques étaient '''orange'''.|The first Atlantic TGV trains were '''orange'''.}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* While prescriptively invariable as a colour name derived from a noun (compare {{m|fr|argent|t=silver}}, {{m|fr|chocolat}}), the nonstandard plural {{m|fr|oranges}} does see use.\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|fr\n|agent orange\n|feu orange\n|hoplostèthe orange\n|jus d'orange\n|orange sanguine\n}}\n\n===See also===\n{{table:colors/fr}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{l|fr|onagre}}, {{l|fr|organe}}, {{l|fr|rongea}}\n\n{{C|fr|Fruits|Oranges}}\n\n==German==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom the noun {{m|de|Orange||orange fruit}}, from {{bor|de|fr|orange}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|de|/oˈʁãːʃ/|/oˈʁaŋʃ/|/oˈʁɔ̃ːʃ/|/oˈʁɔŋʃ/|a=predicative only}}\n* {{IPA|de|/oˈʁãːʒə/|/oˈʁaŋʒə/|/oˈʁɔ̃ːʒə/|/oˈʁɔŋʒə/|a=non-predicative feminine and plural forms}}\n* {{audio|de|De-orange.ogg}}\n* {{audio|de|De-orange2.ogg|a=<<Germany>> (<<Berlin>>)}}\n* {{audio|de|De-orange3.ogg|a=<<Germany>> (<<Berlin>>)}}\n* {{audio|de|De-orange4.ogg|a=<<Germany>> (<<Berlin>>)}}\n* {{audio|de|De-orange5.ogg|a=<<Germany>> (<<Berlin>>)}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{de-adj|stem:+[standard]:orangen[colloquial].comp.sup:orangest[standard]:orangenst[colloquial]}} ''or''<br/>\n{{de-adj|indecl}}\n\n# [[#English|orange]]\n\n====Usage notes====\n* The adjective has two sets of forms. In the formal standard language, endings are added directly to the stem (''orang-''). In less formal style and in the vernacular, another set of forms is used in free variation, in which an ''-n-'' is infixed before the endings.\n* It is also officially correct to leave the adjective entirely undeclined. This usage is rare, however, and seems dated.\n\n====Declension====\n{{de-adecl|stem:+[standard]:orangen[colloquial].comp.sup:orangest[standard]:orangenst[colloquial]}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:de:Duden}}\n* {{R:de:DWDS}}\n\n{{C|de|Colors|Colors of the rainbow|Oranges}}\n\n==Limburgish==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|li|noun|g=f}}\n\n# {{alternative spelling of|li|Orasch|from=Veldeke}}\n\n==Luxembourgish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{dercat|lb|frm|fro}}\n{{bor+|lb|fr|orange}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|lb|/ˈoʁɑ̃ːʃ/}}\n* {{hyph|lb|o|range}}\n* {{homophone|lb|Orange}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{lb-adj|orangen}}\n\n# {{l|en|orange}}\n\n===See also===\n{{table:colors/lb}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* [https://lod.lu/artikel/ORANGE2 \"orange\" in ''LOD'']\n\n{{C|lb|Oranges}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|orenge}}\n\n==Middle French==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|frm|orenge}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|frm|:inh|fro:orenge<id:fruit>|id=fruit|text=+}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{frm-noun|f}}\n\n# {{l|en|orange}} {{gl|fruit of the orange tree}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desctree|fr|orange}}\n* {{desctree|enm|orenge|bor=1}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:DMF}}\n\n{{C|frm|Fruits}}\n\n==Norman==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{l|nrf|oraunge}} {{qualifier|Cotentin}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|nrf|fro|orenge}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|nrf|Jer-orange.ogg|a=Jersey}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{nrf-adj|mf}}\n\n# {{lb|nrf|Jersey|Guernsey}} {{l|en|orange}}\n\n{{topics|nrf|Colors|Oranges}}\n\n==Old French==\n\n===Noun===\n{{fro-noun|f}}\n\n# {{alt form of|fro|orenge}}\n\n==Swedish==\n{{wp|sv:}}\n[[File:Orange Fruit Close-up.jpg|thumb|250px|en '''orange''' {{l|sv|apelsin}} [an '''orange''' orange] ]]\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|sv|fr|orange}}. See {{cog|en|orange}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{q|indefinite common singular}} {{IPA|sv|/ʊˈranɕ/|/ʊˈraŋɧ/|q2=southern}}\n* {{q|indefinite neuter singular}} {{IPA|sv|/ʊˈranɕt/|/ʊˈraŋɧt/|q2=southern}}\n* {{q|definite masculine singular}} {{IPA|sv|/ʊˈranɕɛ/|/ʊˈraŋɧɛ/|q2=southern}}\n* {{q|definite or plural}} {{IPA|sv|/ʊˈranɕa/|/ʊˈraŋɧa/|q2=southern}}\n* {{audio|sv|Sv-orange.ogg}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{head|sv|adjective}}\n\n# [[orange#Adjective|orange]] (orange-coloured)\n#: {{near-syn|sv|brandgul|q=now uncommon}}\n#: {{ux|sv|Hon har långt, '''orange''' hår.|She has long, '''orange''' hair.}}\n\n====Usage notes====\nThe fruit is an {{m|sv|apelsin}}.\n\n====Declension====\n{{sv-adj-irreg|orange|orange|orange|orange|orange|orangeare|orangeaste|orangeaste||orangeaste}}\n:Less common:\n{{sv-adj-irreg|orange|oranget|orange|orangea|orangea|orangeare|orangeaste|orangeaste||orangeaste}}\n{{sv-adj-reg|orange|orangt|orang}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sv-noun}}\n\n# [[orange#Noun|orange]] {{gloss|colour}}\n\n===See also===\n{{table:colors/sv}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:svenska.se|so}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saol}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saob}}\n\n{{C|sv|Colors|Oranges}}"}}